From: Jakub Jirutka <jakub@jirutka.cz>
Date: Tue, 19 May 2026 22:21:45 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] tests: treat zombie kea-lfc as stopped

The Kea shell test cleanup helper waits for killed processes to disappear
from ps output. This breaks when kea-lfc has already exited but remains as a
zombie, because zombies cannot be killed and stay visible until their parent
reaps them.

Treat zombie processes as stopped in the test cleanup path. This avoids a
cascade of unrelated shell test failures after lfc_timer_test, while still
failing for genuinely running processes that do not terminate.

diff --git a/src/lib/testutils/dhcp_test_lib.sh.in b/src/lib/testutils/dhcp_test_lib.sh.in
index b4f479d..cfe062e 100755
--- a/src/lib/testutils/dhcp_test_lib.sh.in
+++ b/src/lib/testutils/dhcp_test_lib.sh.in
@@ -526,6 +526,10 @@ wait_for_process_to_stop() {
     local timeout='4' # seconds
     local deadline="$(($(date +%s) + timeout))"
     while ps "${pid}" >/dev/null; do
+        state="$(ps -o stat= -p "${pid}" 2>/dev/null | awk '{ print $1 }' || true)"
+        case "${state}" in
+            Z*) return 0;;
+        esac
         if test "${deadline}" -lt "$(date +%s)"; then
             # Time is up.
             printf 'ERROR: %s is not stopping.\n' "$(get_process_name "${pid}")" >&2
